      • isCacheable

        Return true if this object instance is cacheable.

      • setCache

        void setCache​(CacheReference obj)
        Assign a cache reference to the class. This is expected to be stored in a static field and used by other methods on the class to return the cached object.

        default boolean decache​(java.lang.String className)
        Allows a cached object to be removed by name.
        Parameters:
        className - simple classname of the object to be removed
        Returns:
        true if the object was actually removed else false
